{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@objc","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"dynamic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"detectionRate","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Su","text":"UInt","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]}],"metadata":{"title":"detectionRate","externalID":"c:@M@ScanbotSDK@objc(cs)SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration(py)detectionRate","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"ScanbotSDK"}],"symbolKind":"property","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"detectionRate","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UInt","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Su"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"detectionRate","kind":"identifier"}]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration\/detectionRate","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK","doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The rate of detections\/recognitions per second in normal performance mode.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Defaults to 20, meaning that 20 frames per second are detected\/recognized, equally distributed over one second.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"When the video frame rate is 30, 10 frames will be skipped and 20 frames will be detected\/recognized.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Note: if you set the detection rate greater to or equal to the video frame rate, no frames will be skipped,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the actual detection rate is limited by the video frame rate.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerenergyconfiguration\/detectionrate"]},{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerenergyconfiguration\/detectionrate"]}],"references":{"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration/detectionRate":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The rate of detections\/recognitions per second in normal performance mode."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Defaults to 20, meaning that 20 frames per second are detected\/recognized, equally distributed over one second."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When the video frame rate is 30, 10 frames will be skipped and 20 frames will be detected\/recognized."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note: if you set the detection rate greater to or equal to the video frame rate, no frames will be skipped,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the actual detection rate is limited by the video frame rate."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"detectionRate"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Su","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UInt"}],"title":"detectionRate","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"detectionRate"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration\/detectionRate","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerenergyconfiguration\/detectionrate"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration":{"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerenergyconfiguration","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The energy management configuration object for a ‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and its subclasses."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and subclasses sport a customizable energy management system."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Since scanners running on a live video feed can put a lot of load onto the CPU and\/or GPU"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the device, causing the battery to drain quickly and running the device hot, you can customize the energy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consumption using this class by configuring the rate of detections\/recognitions per second in performance mode as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"well as in energy saving mode."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In performance mode the scanners will be fed with a higher, configurable rate of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"video frames per second."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After a certain, configurable period of inactivity the energy save mode will be engaged and the rate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of scans will be reduced to a lower (configurable) rate."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can also configure the time of inactivity before the automatic mode switches from performance to energy save mode."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Inactivity here means that both of the following conditions are met:"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration","type":"topic","title":"SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK":{"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Version: 8.0.4","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK","type":"topic","role":"collection","title":"ScanbotSDK"}},"variantOverrides":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"patch":[{"op":"replace","value":"occ","path":"\/identifier\/interfaceLanguage"},{"op":"replace","path":"\/metadata\/roleHeading","value":"Instance Property"},{"op":"replace","path":"\/metadata\/title","value":"detectionRate"},{"op":"replace","path":"\/metadata\/symbolKind","value":"property"},{"op":"replace","path":"\/metadata\/fragments","value":[{"text":"detectionRate","kind":"identifier"}]},{"op":"add","path":"\/topicSections","value":null},{"op":"add","path":"\/relationshipsSections","value":null},{"op":"add","path":"\/seeAlsoSections","value":null},{"op":"replace","path":"\/primaryContentSections\/0","value":{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSUInteger","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"NSUInteger"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"detectionRate"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"}},{"op":"replace","path":"\/references\/doc:~1~1net.doo.ScanbotSDK~1documentation~1ScanbotSDK~1SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration~1detectionRate\/title","value":"detectionRate"},{"op":"replace","path":"\/references\/doc:~1~1net.doo.ScanbotSDK~1documentation~1ScanbotSDK~1SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration~1detectionRate\/fragments","value":[{"text":"detectionRate","kind":"identifier"}]},{"op":"replace","path":"\/references\/doc:~1~1net.doo.ScanbotSDK~1documentation~1ScanbotSDK~1SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration\/title","value":"